node.text:
You think it’s new, a fad, silly … but it’s not … and the behavior of humans And why the long term opportunity is real is based in the fact that we have been pondering this for over a decade. 

Been on … just been waiting for the timing ⏱ to matter to e masses …

We are in the beginning, but this is going to be a fun decade with many ups and downs but web3 is here, please spend 25 hours of learning about the space, it can help many of you get to professional happiness

node.text: I really want people to understand how much of an opportunity there is out here for people with conviction, will, gusto, appetite … because this garage sale flip life shit is game changing, I get emails daily from people who started it and are stunned where they are a year later starting with only $200 … #TrashTalk episode 6 is coming shortly but here is a preview of my best moment. After going ice 🧊 cold 🥶 for 2-3 hours and getting literally nothing in the first 20 sales .. I hit a mother load of Manga Japanese books 📚 for $270 that will go bananas 🍌 on EBay ✅… y’all can do it … please get yours

node.text:
It’s the line that changed my career .. and I hope it helps one of you this Friday morning 🌞 

When I said “lose just as much money” I was referring to this crowd filled with start up founders, many weren’t going to make it, most companies would fail and I was talking to the people in the crowd who are in jobs they hate right now but could quit and get a better job make less but be happy as fuck! ❤️

I remember being in the “green room” feeling a certain energy I never felt before .. I knew the talk was going to go really bad or really Good .. this was the talk that flipped me form a “wine guy” to a entrepreneur that spoke about “perspective, happiness  and opportunity” ..

You think it’s new, a fad, silly … but it’s not … and the behavior of humans And why the long term opportunity is real is based in the fact that we have been pondering this for over a decade. 

Been on … just been waiting for the timing ⏱ to matter to e masses …

We are in the beginning, but this is going to be a fun decade with many ups and downs but web3 is here, please spend 25 hours of learning about the space, it can help many of you get to professional happiness

node.text:
My under 30 year olds friends going into the “real world” I’m telling you 

Figure out how to be patient and don’t have audacity and over expectations and entitlement… it will make you happier and you can adjust if you don’t like how your company or your business is doing at 25/26/27 …

And meet as many people as possible in your interest of choice via digital (zoom/dm) and in real life .. 30 min coffee ..

It’s people and patience that leads to success and happiness for so many in their 30’s

PS: don’t just try to have drinks with superstars in your industry .. do people at your level, below, above ect …

node.text:
Leave the story of what happened in the comments 

Late last night I texted an older friend and it was the best feeling 

Life is about relationships and many of you should just call an old pal 

I know there will be jokes about X’s ect and all that “hahaha shit” but maybe one person will  reconnect with a parent, sibling, former best friend.

Some of you lost top people because of a silly fight and your inability to be the bigger person, you allowed your insecurities to win and lose out on a relationship that mattered to you. Use this short clip as a sign that today is a day to reconnect ❤️❤️❤️❤️

Love always wins, hate or darkness is a trick

node.text:
Be kind ❤️

Gave away all the #MangaBooks I got in TrashTalk episode 6 (link to episode in bio) to people who on 49 minutes noticed showed up outside my office.

I hope many of them flip these books and turn it into a jump start

It was also beyond nice to see so many of you who consume the work and enjoy being part of this community

You can do a lot more by doing things vs talking about how bad / unfair things are .. big shout out to those who took action today … ❤️❤️❤️❤️
